[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the pseudocode walkthrough from Recipe 13.9. It shows one way you could translate those concepts into working Python code using boto3 and the Neptune graph database. It is not production-ready. The real pipeline would handle millions of articles, custom-trained transformer models, and sophisticated conflict resolution. Think of this as the sketch on the whiteboard: useful for understanding the shape of the solution, not something you'd point at PubMed and let rip on Monday morning.
