[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and a few supporting libraries:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 requests gremlinpython opensearch-py
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `comprehend:DetectEntitiesV2` (for biomedical NER)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint` (for custom relation extraction model)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject` (for the document lake)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `sqs:SendMessage` (for the human review queue)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m For Neptune, you'll need network access to the cluster endpoint (Neptune lives in a VPC, so your code must run inside that VPC or use a bastion/VPN). Neptune uses IAM authentication or VPC-level access control rather than traditional credentials.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m For OpenSearch, you'll need the domain endpoint and appropriate IAM permissions (`es:ESHttp*`).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
