[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `fetch_new_articles(last_watermark)`. It queries PubMed's E-utilities API for recently published articles matching our topic filters, then stores the raw XML in S3 for downstream processing.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # PubMed E-utilities base URL. This is a free, public API maintained by NCBI.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Rate limit: 3 requests/second without an API key, 10/second with one.
